{"examples":[{"conversion_notes":"The Python function becomes a top-level Jac ability declared with `def`. The Jac version keeps explicit numeric types and uses a `with entry` block to demonstrate the same call and output without introducing imports or Python-style module code.","jac_code":"def celsius_to_fahrenheit(celsius: float) -> float {
