print(even_numbers([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]))"},{"conversion_notes":"The Python adjacency-list graph is rewritten as an object-spatial Jac graph. Cities are `node` instances connected with `++>`, so the relationship structure is represented directly in the graph instead of being stored in a dictionary of neighbor names.","jac_code":"node City {
